One of my Gadget is built as follow :
{code:java}
gadget.getView().empty();
gadget.getView().append(AJS.$("<div/>").html(args.workedIssues.html));
gadget.resize();
{code}

where *args.workedIssues.html* resulting from REST call, contents HTML with <script> tag for CSS and JS.

With JIRA 4.4-m5, the "Loading" CSS is applied on the 1st Ajax Call (REST "/rest/minyaaTime/1.0/worklog/generate" with result in args.workedIssues.html)
After the REST call, the "Loading" CSS is removed, but when AJS Framework evaluates the added HTML, the call done <script> tags for JS, as Ajax calls. the "Loading" CSS is added and never removed. I add diffculty to debug AJS to understand why the Ajax calls returns do not raise hideLoading().

I found this workaround ...
{code:java}
gadget.getView().empty();
gadget.getView().append(AJS.$("<div/>").html(args.workedIssues.html));
gadget.resize();
gadget.hideLoading();
{code}

